Convert the recipe into a concise Markdown paragraph with European units,
using grams for all ingredients. For the first mention of each ingredient,
use the format `{quantity g {ingredient_id}}` where ingredient_id is a pyfooda
canonical id (snake_case, e.g. liver, natto, brown_rice, sardine).

Add metadata on line 2: `<!-- quick:MINUTES -->` (cook time in minutes).
Add a photo line: `![Recipe Title](images/{day}_{meal}_{version}.jpg)`

Rules:
- 1-person meal, 700–1000 calories
- Maximum 5-6 tracked ingredients per recipe
- Prioritize nutrient-dense and unconventional foods (liver, natto, sardines,
  herring, kidney, bone marrow, oysters, anchovies, cod liver, kimchi, miso)
- Quick recipes (5–25 minutes)
- Only use ingredients from pyfooda: run `pf.find_ingredients("query")` to check
- No {{untracked}} ingredients — every ingredient must have grams

Example:

```markdown
# Liver Bolognese
<!-- quick:20 -->

Finely chop {80g {onion}} and {5g {garlic}}. Sauté in {15g {olive_oil}} until soft.
Add {150g {liver}} and {100g {beef}}, cook 5 minutes. Stir in {200g {tomato}} and
simmer 10 minutes. Toss with {180g {pasta}}.
```
